{"title_page": "Baghuwar, Madhya Pradesh", "text_new": "'''Baghuwar''' or Baghuvar is also pronounced as (Devanagari: \u092c\u0918\u0941\u0935\u093e\u0930) is a village located in the Kareli block of Narsinghpur district in the state of Madhya Pradesh of India. The village falls under the division of Jabalpur and positioned at a  distance of 201 km from the state capital of Bhopal.\n\n==In The News==\nIt is the only village in India that has an existence since independence and that too without a sarpanch. Each & every house in the village has its common toilet complex that is used for social gatherings. The sewage lines are also there in the village. In order to cook food and light up the village, the produced gas is used.<ref>{{cite web |title=15 Inspiring Indian Villages That Are Showing the Way Forward |url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/85354/inspiring-indian-villages-sustainable-development/ |website=thebetterindia.com}}</ref>\n\n==Demographic==\nThe Baghwar/Baghwar Census Location Code Number of 2001 is 04812000 and Census Location Code Number of 2011 is 491371. The total area of the village is 906.7 hectares in which total population was 1946 in which number of households were 465.\n==References==\n", "text_old": "'''Baghuwar''' or Baghuvar is also pronounced as (Devanagari: \u092c\u0918\u0941\u0935\u093e\u0930) is a village located in the Kareli block of Narsinghpur district in the state of Madhya Pradesh of India. The village falls under the division of Jabalpur and positioned at a  distance of 201 km from the state capital of Bhopal.\n\n==In The News==\nIt is the only village in India that has an existence since independence and that too without a sarpanch. Each & every house in the village has its common toilet complex that is used for social gatherings. The sewage lines are also there in the village. In order to cook food and light up the village, the produced gas is used.<ref>{{cite web |title=15 Inspiring Indian Villages That Are Showing the Way Forwar