ths later on 24 April 2010, Leigertwood scored his fifth goal of the season, in a 1\u20130 win over Barnsley.<ref>{{cite news|title=Barnsley 0\u20131 Queens Park Rangers|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_1/8632320.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|date=24 April 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> Despite missing out several matches, due to injury and suspension,<ref>{{cite news|title= QPR reveal swine flu cases|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/football-league/qpr-reveal-swine-flu-cases-1811316.html|publisher=The Independent|date=29 October 2009|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=QPR's Jay Simpson has to prove a point against Ipswich|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/qprs-jay-simpson-has-to-prove-a-point-against-ipswich-6709578.html|publisher=London Evening Standard|date=9 February 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=QPR skipper fit for Sheffield United clash|url=https://www.mylondon.news/sport/football/football-news/leigertwood-signs-new-rangers-deal-6001306|publisher=My London News|date=11 March 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> he went on to make forty\u2013five appearances and scoring five times in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2010\u201311 season, Leigertwood found his playing his time at Queens Park Rangers reduced and mostly came on as a substitute.<ref>{{cite news|title=Queens Park Rangers fans forced me out - Leigertwood|url=https://www.mylondon.news/sport/other-sport/qpr-fans-forced-out---5985299|publisher=My London News|date=1 June 2011|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=QPR midfielder Mikele Leigertwood happy with Reading|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/r/reading/9252870.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|date=3 October 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=Warnock to let Mikele go|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11711/6579522/warnock-to-let-mikele-go|publisher=Sky Sports|date=15 December 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> As a result, he was fallen out of favour with [[Neil Warnock]].<ref>{{cite news|title=QPR midfielder Mikele Leigertwood happy with Reading|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/r/reading/9252870.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|date=3 December 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> By the time of his departure, he went on to make nine appearances for the side in the 2010\u201311 season. During his time at Queens Park Rangers, he made 141 appearances and 12 goals for Queens Park Rangers.\n\n===Reading===\n[[File:Mikele Leigertwood, 02 01 12.jpg|thumb|left|400px|Leigertwood being marked by [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]]'s [[Aron Gunnarsson]] during the Cardiff City and [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] match on 2 January 2012.]]\n\nLeigertwood went on loan to [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] for two months on 23 November 2010.<ref>{{cite news|title=Queens Park Rangers loan Leigertwood to Reading|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/r/reading/9217839.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|date=23 November 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> On 27 November 2010, he made his Reading debut, starting the match before coming off in the 77th minutes, in a 0\u20130 draw against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Reading 0\u20130 Leeds United|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_1/9220886.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 November 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> Leigertwood quickly became a first team regular for the side.<ref>{{cite news|title=Howard desperate for Reading FC recall at Sheffield United|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/howard-desperate-reading-fc-recall-4218898|publisher=Get Reading|date=1 December 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=Reading FC's Tabb hopes to make his mark against old pals|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/reading-fcs-tabb-hopes-make-4219055|publisher=Get Reading|date=9 December 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=Jem Karacan aims to silence Robbie Savage|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/jem-karacan-aims-silence-robbie-4219223|publisher=Get Reading|date=17 December 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> After a series of consistently good performances, this was extended to the end of the 2010\u201311 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Shane Long shines for Reading FC|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/news/local-news/shane-long-shines-reading-fc-4217826|publisher=Get Reading|date=4 January 2011|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=Reading extend loan of midfielder Mikele Leigertwood|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/r/reading/9358549.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|date=11 January 2011|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club against [[Stevenage F.C.|Stevenage]] in the FA Cup on 29 January 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stevenage 1-2 Reading: Late Long winner kills off Cup fairytale|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/stevenage-1-2-reading-fa-cup-3337006|publisher=Daily Mirror|date=29 January 2011|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> A week later Leigertwood added another goal to his tally with a 21st minute deflected strike against [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] in a 2\u20132 draw.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cardiff City 2\u20132 Reading|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_1/9379856.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|date=1 February 2011|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> During the match, Leigertwood punched [[Michael Chopra]] \"after a confrontation involving both sets of players, but immediately admitted his part in the melee\" and served a three match suspension.<ref>{{cite news|title=Punch by Reading FC star on Cardiff player led to ban|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/punch-reading-fc-star-cardiff-4216808|publisher=Get Reading|date=3 February 2011|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> After serving a three match suspension, his performance earned him Reading Post AHG