012|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=Tabb keen to avoid play-off heartbreak|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/tabb-keen-avoid-play-off-heartbreak-4202889|publisher=Get Reading|date=1 March 2012|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> His second goal of the campaign came at home to [[Leicester City F.C|Leicester City]] in a 3\u20131 win, and this was followed up with strikes against [[Blackpool F.C|Blackpool]] and [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] as [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] surged towards promotion with an incredible run of games of which Leigertwood was an important figure in.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reading 3\u20131 Leicester City|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17243538|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 March 2012|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=Reading 3\u20131 Blackpool|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17412322|publisher=BBC Sport|date=23 March 2012|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=Reading FC goal scoring record a real team effort|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/reading-fc-goal-scoring-record-4203364|publisher=Get Reading|date=27 March 2012|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=West Ham United 2\u20134 Reading|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17497330|publisher=BBC Sport|date=30 March 2012|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> After returning from a knee injury, he returned to the starting lineup, where he key role Leigertwood had played was rewarded when he scored the winning goal in a 1\u20130 victory at home to [[Nottingham Forest F.C|Nottingham Forest]], which secured Reading's promotion back to the top flight after a four-year absence.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reading FC can handle Southampton FC dangerman Rickie Lambert|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/reading-fc-can-handle-southampton-4202002|publisher=Get Reading|date=13 April 2012|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=Reading FC promo