eading F.C. season|2013\u201314]]\n|4||0||0||0||0||0||0||0||4||0\n|-\n!Total\n!97!!7!!7!!2!!2!!1!!3!!0!!109!!10\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Career totals\n!372!!21!!20!!2!!17!!2!!7!!0!!416!!25\n|}\n\n{{refbegin}}\n:A.&nbsp;{{note|League}} The \"League\" column constitutes appearances and goals (including those as a substitute) in the [[Premier League]] and [[the Football League]].\n:B.&nbsp;{{note|Other}} The \"Other\" column constitutes appearances and goals (including those as a substitute) in the [[Football League play-offs|play-offs]].\n{{refend}}\n\n===International===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!colspan=3|[[Antigua and Barbuda national football team|Antigua and Barbuda]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Mikele Leigertwood|url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/28934/Mikele_Leigertwood.html|website=national-football-teams.com|publisher=National Football Teams|accessdate=11 November 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2008||3||1\n|-\n|2009||0||0\n|-\n|2010||3||0\n|-\n|2011||3||0\n|-\n|2012||2||0\n|-\n!Total||11||1\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ '''<big>Mikele Leigertwood: International Goals</big>'''\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1 || 7 November 2008 || [[Marvin Lee Stadium]], [[Macoya]], [[Trinidad and Tobago]] || {{fb|GUY}} || '''1'''\u20130 || 2-1 || [[2008 Caribbean Championship]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Personal life==\nIn March 2010, Leigertwood was involved in the Kick It Out's latest campaign, which aims to raise awareness of homophobia in football.<ref>{{cite news|title=QPR man Leigertwood backs Kick It Out campaign|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/local/london/hi/people_and_places/newsid_8551000/8551698.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|date=5 March 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> During his time at Reading, he became the Royals' 'Reading Stars' ambassador.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2013/march/a-chance-reading-stars/|title=A CHANCE: READING STARS|publisher=Reading F.C.|date=21 March 2013|accessdate=24 August 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190824134016/https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2013/march/a-chance-reading-stars/|archivedate=24 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nGrowing up, he supported [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Mikele Leigertwood is gunning for Spurs|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/mikele-leigertwood-gunning-spurs-4196911|publisher=Get Reading|date=14 September 2012|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> Leigertwood is good friends with [[Jobi McAnuff]], having known each other since school and were teammates at Wimbledon, Crystal Palace and Reading.<ref>{{cite news|title=QPR midfielder open to permanent Reading FC switch|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/qpr-midfielder-open-permanent-reading-4220385|publisher=Get Reading|date=24 November 2010|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=McAnuff can rely on school pal|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/mcanuff-can-rely-school-pal-4211604|publisher=Get Reading|date=15 July 2011|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> He's a father of two children.<ref>{{cite news|title=Leigertwood warns Crystal Palace there will be no hangovers at Reading FC|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/leigertwood-warns-crystal-palace-no-4202140|publisher=Get Reading|date=20 April 2012|accessdate=24 August 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=Leigertwood dedicated thunderbolt to newborn son|url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/leigertwood-dedicated-thunderbolt-newborn-son-4196103|publisher=Get Reading|date=29 October 2012|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n=== Club ===\n;[[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]]\n* [[Football League Championship]] (1): [[2010\u201311 Football League Championship|2010\u201311]]\n\n;[[Reading F.C.|Reading]]\n* [[Football League Championship]]: [[2011\u201312 Football League Championship|2011\u201312]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20121020185729/http://www.readingfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/index.aspx?playerid=232581&tcmuri=41347 Official profile at Reading FC]\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*[http://caribbeanfootballdatabase.com/antiguaandbarbuda/players/mikeleleigertwood.html International Statistics] at CaribbeanFootballDatabase\n\n<!--{{SQUAD TEMPLATE GOES HERE}}-->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leigertwood, Mikele}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Enfield Town]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Antigua and Barbuda footballers]]\n[[Category:Antigua and Barbuda international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Wimbledon F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Leyton Orient F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Crystal Palace F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Sheffield United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Queens Park Rangers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:English people of Antigua and Barbuda descent]]\n[[Category:Reading F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Black British sportspeople]]\n", "name_user": "Keith D", "label": "safe", "comment": "Space", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mikele_Leigertwood"}
